 Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 2 || 25 April 1990 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|TCH}} || 4\u20132 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 3, 4 || 18 November 1992 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|TUR}} || 4\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 2\n|-\n| 5 || 31 March 1993 || [[\u0130zmir Atat\u00fcrk Stadium]], [[\u0130zmir]], Turkey || {{fb|TUR}} || 2\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 6 || 8 September 1993 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|POL}} || 3\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 7 || 23 May 1996 || [[Workers' Stadium]], [[Beijing]], China || {{fb|CHN}} || 3\u20130 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 8 || 15 June 1996 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|SCO}} || 2\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 1996|Euro 1996 finals]] || 1\n|-\n| 9 || 1 September 1996 || [[Stadionul Republican|Republican Stadium]], [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]], Moldova || {{fb|MDA}} || 3\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification|1998 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 10 || 10 September 1997 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|MDA}} || 4\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification|1998 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Newcastle United'''\n*[[FA Youth Cup]]: 1984\u201385<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Tottenham Hotspur'''\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[1990\u201391 FA Cup|1990\u201391]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Rangers'''\n*[[Scottish Football League Premier Division|Scottish Premier Division]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish Premier Division|1995\u201396]], [[1996\u201397 Scottish Premier Division|1996\u201397]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[Scottish Cup]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish Cup|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish League Cup|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Middlesbrough'''\n*[[Football League Cup]] runner-up: [[1997\u201398 Football League Cup|1997\u201398]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[PFA Young Player of the Year]]: [[PFA Young Player of the Year#Winners|1987\u201388]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[PFA Team of the Year|PFA First Division Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year#1987\u201388|1987\u201388]], [[PFA Team of the Year#1990\u201391|1990\u201391]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[1990 FIFA World Cup#All-star team|1990 FIFA World Cup All-star team]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/377316/1990-world-cup-all-star-team-who-were-players-voted-best-italy-180523283751/ |title= 1990 World Cup All-Star Team: Who were the players voted best in Italy? |last=Hawkins |first=Billy |date=10 June 2018 |website= talksport.com |access-date=25 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[BBC Sports Personality of the Year]]: [[BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award#Winners|1990]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[Ballon d'Or]]: [[1990 Ballon d'Or|1990]] (4th)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy90.html |title=European Footballer of the Year (\"Ballon d'Or\") 1990 |publisher=RSSSF |date=26 March 2005 |accessdate=24 October 2016 |first=Pierrend |last=Jos\u00e9 Luis}}</ref>\n*[[BBC Goal of the Season]]: 1990\u201391<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[PFA Scotland Players' Player of the Year]]: [[1995\u201396 in Scottish football#Individual honours|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[SFWA Footballer of the Year]]: [[1995\u201396 in Scottish football#Individual honours|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[UEFA European Championship awards#Team of the Tournament|UEFA European Championship Team of the Tournament]]: [[UEFA European Football Championship Teams of the Tournament#England 1996|1996]]<ref>{{cite web |title=European Championships \u2013 UEFA Teams of Tournament |url=http://rsssf.com/miscellaneous/euro-uefatot.html |website=rsssf.com |accessdate=5 October 2014}}</ref>\n*[[English Football Hall of Fame]] Inductee: 2002<ref name=\"nfm\" />\n*[[List of Rangers F.C. players|Rangers Hall of Fame]] Inductee: 2006 <ref>{{cite web |title=Profile |url=http://www.rangers.co.uk/club/history/hall-of-fame/item/599-paul-gascoigne |publisher=rangers.co.uk |accessdate=26 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326151111/http://www.rangers.co.uk/club/history/hall-of-fame/item/599-paul-gascoigne|archive-date=26 March 2014|url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n===Specific===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{Refbegin}}\n*{{Citation |last=Charlton |first=Jack |first2=Peter |last2=Byrne |title=The Autobiography |publisher=[[Transworld Publishers|Partridge Press]] |year=1996 |isbn=1-85225-256-1 |ref={{harvid|Charlton|1996}} |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/autobiography0000char }}\n* {{cite book | last = Clark | first = Lee| title = Black or White No Grey Areas | publisher = Mojo Risin' Publishing | year = 2016| location = Newcastle| language = English| isbn = 9780993442452| ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Ferris | first = Paul| title = The Boy on the Shed | publisher = Hodder & Stoughton | year = 2018| location = United Kingdom| language = English| isbn = 9781473666726| ref = harv}}\n* {{Cite book |first=Paul |last=Gascoigne |first2=Hunter |last2=Davies |author2link=Hunter Davies |year=2004 |title=Gazza: My Story |edition= |publisher=Headline Publishing |location=London |isbn=0-7472-7118-6 |ref={{harvid|Gascoigne|2004}} |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/gazzamystory0000gasc }}\n* {{Cite book |first=Paul |last=Gascoigne |first2=John |last2=McKeown |first3=Hunter |last3=Davies |year=2006 |title=Being Gazza: Tackling My Demons |edition= |publisher=Headline Publishing |location=London |isbn=0-7553-1542-1 |ref={{harvid|Gascoigne|2006}}}}\n*{{cite book | last = Gascoigne| first = Paul| author-link = | title = Gazza: My Story| publisher = Hachette| year = 2014| location = United Kingdom| pages = | language =English  | isbn = 9781472220639| ref= harv}}\n*{{cite book | last = Jones| first = Vinnie | author-link = | title = It's Been Emotional\n| publisher =Simon and Schuster | series = | volume = | edition = | date = 26 September 2013| location = United Kingdom | language = English | ref =harv | isbn = 9781471127601}}\n* {{cite web | url = https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/gazza-untold-stories-need-know-tales-launched-a-legend-0| title = Gazza, the untold stories: the need-to-know tales that launched a legend| last = Fourfourtwo staff| first = | date = 17 April 2018| website = fourfourtwo| publisher = | access-date = 24 July 2019| ref = {{harvid|Fourfourtwo staff|2018}}}}\n* {{cite web | url = https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/gennaro-gattuso-he-was-really-breaking-my-balls-so-i-lost-my-temper-and-stuck-a-fork-his | title = Gennaro Gattuso, Blue Ranger | last = Gattuso | first =Gennaro | date = 5 April 2018| website = fourfourtwo| publisher = | access-date = 15 March 2020| ref = harv}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{FIFA player}}\n*{{youtube|-cWzY20VyMA|Spitting Image: \"The Gazza Song\"}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = England squads\n| bg = white\n| fg = #CF081F\n| bordercolor = #0B0B3F\n| list1 = \n{{England squad 1990 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad UEFA Euro 1996}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = Gold\n| fg = Navy\n| list1 = \n{{1987\u201388 Football League First Division PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{1990\u201391 Football League First Division PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{1990 FIFA World Cup Team of the Tournament}}\n{{UEFA Euro 1996 Team of the Tournament}}\n{{Goal of the Season}}\n{{PFA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{Newcastle United F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{Tottenham Hotspur F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{BBC Sports Personali