bley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|TCH}} || 4\u20132 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 3, 4 || 18 November 1992 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|TUR}} || 4\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 2\n|-\n| 5 || 31 March 1993 || [[\u0130zmir Atat\u00fcrk Stadium]], [[\u0130zmir]], Turkey || {{fb|TUR}} || 2\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 6 || 8 September 1993 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|POL}} || 3\u20130 || [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|1994 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 7 || 23 May 1996 || [[Workers' Stadium]], [[Beijing]], China || {{fb|CHN}} || 3\u20130 || Friendly || 1\n|-\n| 8 || 15 June 1996 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|SCO}} || 2\u20130 || [[UEFA Euro 1996|Euro 1996 finals]] || 1\n|-\n| 9 || 1 September 1996 || [[Stadionul Republican|Republican Stadium]], [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]], Moldova || {{fb|MDA}} || 3\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification|1998 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|-\n| 10 || 10 September 1997 || [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley Stadium]], [[London]], England || {{fb|MDA}} || 4\u20130 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification|1998 World Cup qualifier]] || 1\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Newcastle United'''\n*[[FA Youth Cup]]: 1984\u201385<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Tottenham Hotspur'''\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[1990\u201391 FA Cup|1990\u201391]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n\n'''Rangers'''\n*[[Scottish Football League Premier Division|Scottish Premier Division]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish Premier Division|1995\u201396]], [[1996\u201397 Scottish Premier Division|1996\u201397]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[Scottish Cup]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish Cup|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[1995\u201396 Scottish League Cup|1995\u201396]]<ref name=\"Paul John Gascoigne\"/